714833f-a.text:
93rd Street, south side, east from and including Third Avenue.
June 26, 1931.
P. L. Sperr.

708138f-a.text:
Third Avenue, east side, north from E. 93rd Street, showing tenements lining this thoroughfare. This vicinity is between those Manhattan localities, Yorkville and Harlem and is better known as lower Harlem. Note the Third Avenue "El" structure in the center
of this thoroughfare.
September 14, 1938.
~.L. Sperr

708139f-a.text:
Third Avenue, at the S.E. corner of E. 94th Street, showing a clearance at same across which the photographer is viewing to show the clock tower atop a unit of Ruppert's Brewery. This structure is on the south side of E. 93rd Street between Third and Second Avenue. Note the "El" on the thoroughfare from
which it receives its popular name.
September 13, 1938.
P.L. Sperr
